Chile Picks Claudio Borghi to Lead National Soccer Team, La Tercera Says

-- B y   R a n d y   W o o d s
-- 
2011-02-24T11:55:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-24/chile-picks-claudio-borghi-to-lead-national-soccer-team-la-tercera-says.html
Chile’s professional soccer club
association selected Claudio Borghi to replace Marcelo Bielsa as
head coach of the national team,  La Tercera  reported today.  Borghi, who previously coached Chilean soccer club Colo-
Colo, will receive an annual salary of almost $1.5 million, the
Santiago-based newspaper  reported , without saying where it
obtained the information.  Chile’s national team is ranked fourteenth in the world by
FIFA, the sport’s global governing body.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Woods in Santiago at 
 rwoods13@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bill Faries at 
 wfaries@bloomberg.net  